the rain] a lifeless land...\"; some nations would like those who are far from a habitat with water, as opposed to the inhabitants of jurisdictions because [the latter] are [already] near the stream-beds and the rivers and the springs, so they are in no need of [and have already] overcome [the dependency upon] irrigation of rainwater […]"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣa.niː/","/ɣa.nijj/"]}